					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th to 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>317 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>225</height>
										<width>170</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>142</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>317 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 vellum and 2 paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>32 quires: i-xxiv11 (folios 1-240); xxv12 (folios 241-152); xxvi-xxxi10 (folios 253-312); xxxii6-1 (folios 313-317). Marked by catchwords at the end of the quires and Hebrew letters at the beginning of the quires (mostly cut away).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Incomplete at the end.</p>
									<p>Folio 2 damaged.</p>
									<p>Stained. Slightly water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling and pricking.</p>
									<p>Last line written outside ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter initials given in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Quire catchwords enclosed in simple pen and ink designs.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
